.Dd March 28, 2026
.Dt KATADM 8
.Os openXao
.Sh NAME
.Nm katadm
.Nd administrative tool for the Kernel Access Table
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm load | clear | status
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility manages the rules within the KAT kernel module. 
Rules are typically read from
.Pa /etc/kat.conf .
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Cm load
Parses
.Pa /etc/kat.conf
and uploads rules to the kernel via
.Pa /dev/kat .
.It Cm clear
Flushes all rules from the kernel's in-memory table.
.It Cm status
Displays the number of active rules currently enforced by the kernel.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "/etc/kat.conf" -compact
.It Pa /etc/kat.conf
The default configuration file. Format is
.Li uid:path:privmask .
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr kat 1 ,
.Xr kat 4
